  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nYesterday I saw a missed attestation in my validator, I checked and found that my beacon has the error: double free or corruption (out) at 13:30:16. Before that beacon has been running fine with consistent +-50 peers.\r\n\r\nIt restarted immediately and after that beacon running as usual.\r\n\r\nContext: beacon running fine since 1st Dec before genesis and never got problem until this.\r\n\r\nMy system: Ubuntu desktop 20.04 LTS. Running beacon, validator and geth. 32GB ram and 1TB nvme SSD on Intel NUC10FNK\r\n![beaconerrordetail](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44791194/101346713-ee234880-38c3-11eb-936b-bc2efb9e44a8.png)\r\n![validator error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/44791194/101346861-27f44f00-38c4-11eb-9b33-63a2c70e420f.png)\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nv1.0.3. I downloaded the binary from github lighthouse-v1.0.3-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz and runs it as a service file. ExecStart command (following Somer's guide, but I added metrics) =/usr/local/bin/lighthouse bn --network mainnet --datadir /var/lib/lighthouse --staking --metrics --eth1-endpoints http://127.0.0.1:8545,http://infura-endpoint,http://alchemy-endpoint\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nIt auto-restart and running normally now\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
